                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.355,
                                "byte_start": 73956,
                                "byte_stop": 107393,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 89-5011, Powers against Ohio will be announced by Justice Kennedy."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.355,
                        "stop": 265.665,
                        "byte_start": 107393,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15113,
                            "name": "Anthony M. Kennedy",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/anthony_m_kennedy",
                            "last_name": "Kennedy",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2757,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 572162400,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2757"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32679,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 47100,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/anthony_kennedy_1_3.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10147,
                            "identifier": "anthony_m_kennedy"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.355,
                                "stop": 12.006,
                                "byte_start": 107393,
                                "byte_stop": 122021,
                                "text": "Our decision in Powers versus Ohio is summarized as follows:"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 12.006,
                                "stop": 18.585,
                                "byte_start": 122021,
                                "byte_stop": 148353,
                                "text": "The case concerns the prosecution\u0027s use of preemptory challenges in the jury selection process."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.585,
                                "stop": 30.27,
                                "byte_start": 148353,
                                "byte_stop": 195060,
                                "text": "In 1986, we ruled that in a criminal case, a prosecutor could not use the preemptory challenge as a way to remove jurors of the same race as the defendant where race was the reason for the challenge."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.27,
                                "stop": 33.243,
                                "byte_start": 195060,
                                "byte_stop": 206972,
                                "text": "That case was Batson versus Kentucky."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 33.243,
                                "stop": 45.326,
                                "byte_start": 206972,
                                "byte_stop": 255350,
                                "text": "Today, we must decide whether the rule in Batson applies so that a defendant in a criminal case can object to the race-based exclusion of the juror where the perspective juror and the defendant are not of the same race."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.326,
                                "stop": 48.913,
                                "byte_start": 255350,
                                "byte_stop": 269665,
                                "text": "The case comes to us on a certiorari to the Supreme Court of the State of Ohio."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.913,
                                "stop": 56.55,
                                "byte_start": 269665,
                                "byte_stop": 300176,
                                "text": "The petitioner, one Larry Powers, was convicted in Ohio of murder and other related counts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.55,
                                "stop": 65.648,
                                "byte_start": 300176,
                                "byte_stop": 336643,
                                "text": "At his trial, he sought to object when the prosecution used seven different challenges to remove Black persons from the jury selection panel."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.648,
                                "stop": 68.397,
                                "byte_start": 336643,
                                "byte_stop": 347615,
                                "text": "Powers himself is White."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 68.397,
                                "stop": 72.388,
                                "byte_start": 347615,
                                "byte_stop": 363602,
                                "text": "He sought a hearing to determine whether the challenges were racially motivated."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.388,
                                "stop": 79.185,
                                "byte_start": 363602,
                                "byte_stop": 390769,
                                "text": "The Trial Court and the Ohio reviewing courts held that he could not raise a Batson type objection."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.185,
                                "stop": 80.864,
                                "byte_start": 390769,
                                "byte_stop": 397456,
                                "text": "We now reverse."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.864,
                                "stop": 87.501,
                                "byte_start": 397456,
                                "byte_stop": 423997,
                                "text": "The individual juror has a right not to be excluded by a prosecution challenge that is based on the juror\u0027s race."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 87.501,
                                "stop": 97.436,
                                "byte_start": 423997,
                                "byte_stop": 463703,
                                "text": "The opportunity for ordinary citizens to participate in the administration of justice has long been recognized as one of the principal justifications for the jury system."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.436,
                                "stop": 106.168,
                                "byte_start": 463703,
                                "byte_stop": 498707,
                                "text": "Juries preserve the democratic element of the law by guarding the rights of the parties and insuring continued acceptance of the laws by all the people."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.168,
                                "stop": 115.3,
                                "byte_start": 498707,
                                "byte_stop": 535174,
                                "text": "But the exception of voting, for most citizens, the honor and privilege of jury duty is their most significant opportunity to participate in the democratic process."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 115.3,
                                "stop": 132.245,
                                "byte_start": 535174,
                                "byte_stop": 602988,
                                "text": "While an individual juror does not have a right to sit on any particular petit jury, the Equal Protection Clause prohibits a prosecutor from using the state\u0027s preemptory challenges to exclude otherwise qualified and unbiased persons from the jury solely by reason of their race."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 132.245,
                                "stop": 147.066,
                                "byte_start": 602988,
                                "byte_stop": 662234,
                                "text": "We do not believe that race-based preemptory challenges survive equal protection scrutiny because members of all races are subject to like treatment which is to say that White jurors are subject to the same risk of discriminatory exclusion as our jurors of other races."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 147.066,
                                "stop": 155.212,
                                "byte_start": 662234,
                                "byte_stop": 694834,
                                "text": "It is actually emetic that racial classifications do not become legitimate on the assumption that all person suffer them in equal degree."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 155.212,
                                "stop": 164.087,
                                "byte_start": 694834,
                                "byte_stop": 730361,
                                "text": "We further hold that the defendant in a criminal case has requisite standing to challenge the prosecution\u0027s racially discriminatory exclusion of jurors."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 164.087,
                                "stop": 167.996,
                                "byte_start": 730361,
                                "byte_stop": 746034,
                                "text": "The discrimination causes the defendant a cognizable injury."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167.996,
                                "stop": 176.164,
                                "byte_start": 746034,
                                "byte_stop": 778635,
                                "text": "The injury arises not because the individual jurors dismissed by the prosecution may had been predisposed to favor the defendant."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.164,
                                "stop": 179.927,
                                "byte_start": 778635,
                                "byte_stop": 793682,
                                "text": "If that were true, the jurors might have been excluded for cause."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 179.927,
                                "stop": 190.63,
                                "byte_start": 793682,
                                "byte_stop": 836523,
                                "text": "Rather, it is because of the intrusion of racial discrimination into the jury selection process casts doubt on the integrity of the entire trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 190.63,
                                "stop": 201.778,
                                "byte_start": 836523,
                                "byte_stop": 881140,
                                "text": "The prosecutor\u0027s wrongful exclusion of a juror by a race-based preemptory challenge is a constitutional violation committed in open court at the outset of the proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 201.778,
                                "stop": 218.243,
                                "byte_start": 881140,
                                "byte_stop": 946968,
                                "text": "Active discrimination by a prosecutor condones violation of the United States Constitution within the very institution entrusted with its enforcement and so invites cynicism respecting the jury\u0027s neutrality in its obligation to adhere to the law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 218.243,
                                "stop": 229.069,
                                "byte_start": 946968,
                                "byte_stop": 990332,
                                "text": "The purpose of the jury system is to impress upon the criminal defendant and the community as a whole that a verdict of conviction or acquittal is given in accordance with the law by persons who are fair."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 229.069,
                                "stop": 237.216,
                                "byte_start": 990332,
                                "byte_stop": 1022828,
                                "text": "The verdict will not be accepted or understood in these terms if the jury is chosen by unlawful means at the outset."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 237.216,
                                "stop": 243.673,
                                "byte_start": 1022828,
                                "byte_stop": 1048741,
                                "text": "We, thus, find that a criminal defendant may challenge the exclusion of jurors on account of race."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 243.673,
                                "stop": 254.822,
                                "byte_start": 1048741,
                                "byte_stop": 1093254,
                                "text": "To bar a petitioner\u0027s claim because of his race differs from that of the excluded jurors would be to condone the arbitrary exclusion of citizens from the duty, honor, and privilege of jury service."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 254.822,
                                "stop": 259.976,
                                "byte_start": 1093254,
                                "byte_stop": 1113943,
                                "text": "The case is remanded to the Ohio courts for further proceedings not inconsistent with this opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 259.976,
                                "stop": 265.665,
                                "byte_start": 1113943,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed a dissenting opinion and is joined by the Chief Justice."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
